It was also pointed out that the journalists who most struggle with trauma are not necessarily the ones who are out ‚Äúin the field‚Äù but can be those watching distressing footage at their desks.

I was pleased that freelancers and casuals were thought of during the conversation because as well as everything staff journos face, we have the added disadvantage of not being able to access company resources plus don‚Äôt want to say anything for fear of not being asked back.

It was great to meet other journalists today over Zoom and to be able to speak openly about MH and wellbeing. Journalists, & especially news reporters, are meant to be hardcore and push emotions down to get the story but we still need to process things we have seen/heard.

I attended a great workshop on mental health for journalists organised by @HeadlinesNet today. @sianwilliams100 did a talk about trauma and resilience & the barriers that stop journalists from speaking up if they struggle. Well facilitated by the @mrjohncrowley & @HANNAHSTORM6 ..
